@melloware  The JSDocs basically look good to me. If it compiles with the -P jsdoc profile, it should be fine.
One minor thing though: js-cookie has semi-official type declarations on DefinitelyTyped. Currently, these are for version 2.2 (as js-cookie has only a release candidate of version 3 so far). Eventually we should just use that (installed via npm during the build process).
In preparation for that, it would be good to rename the namespace and interface so that it matches what's on DefinitelyTyped:
declare namespace Cookies {
	/**
	 * Represents the properties of a cookie, other that its name and value.
	 */
	export interface CookieAttributes {
        }
}
(and change the parts in core.js accordingly)
